name: Cybele Cuff
description:
Our Cybele cuff is hand made and inspired by ancient beliefs in the powers of snakeskin.
The snake has long played a part in the imagery from which magic is made. People of many cultures consider them an emblem of long life. Ancient Romans often wore serpent arm bands as protective and luck-bringing jewelry.
In religion, mythology, and literature, serpents and snakes represent fertility or a creative life force. As snakes shed their skin they are symbols of rebirth, transformation, immortality, and healing.

Antique gold finished brass cuff
Cuff measures 6 inches in length
2 1/4 inch at widest tapers to 1 inch at ends

Please allow 2 weeks as each cuff is handmade
